cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with automatic segmentation of biomedical images. The use of adversarial neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The focus on domain adaptation suggests that it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of MR databases suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
